<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="266" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[174,1233,239,618]" pageId="1" pageNumber="266">
Diagnosis. Head longer than broad; postocular setae well developed, with apices expanded. Antenna 8-segmented, segment III with one outer sense cone but never with an inner sense cone, IV with one inner and one or two outer sense cones, VIII usually non-pedicellate. Mouthcone narrowly pointed. Maxillary stylets retracted far into the head, maxillary bridge absent. Pronotum weakly sculptured; all pronotal setae well developed, with apices expanded; basantral plates absent. Metanotum longitudinally striate to hexagonally reticulate; mesopresternum divided or undivided; metathoracic sternopleural sutures present. Fore tarsus with tooth in both sexes. Fore wing parallel sided, duplicated cilia present. Pelta bell-shaped to triangular. Abdominal tergites IIâ€“VII with 2 pairs of sigmoid wing retaining setae; tergite IX with S1 and S2 setae well developed and expanded apically in both sexes. Tube shorter than head. Male with a broad pore plate on abdominal sternite VIII (
<bibRefCitation author="Tyagi, K. &amp; Kumar, V." box="[334,618,591,618]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="266" pagination="21 - 31" part="2803" refId="ref1905" refString="Tyagi, K., Kumar, V. 2011. The Indian species of Liophloeothrips Priesner (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae) with one new species. Zootaxa, 2803, 21 - 31." title="The Indian species of Liophloeothrips Priesner (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripidae) with one new species" type="journal article" year="2011">Tyagi and Kumar, 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
